  "texts": [
    "If there are regions, there must be boundaries between the regions.",
    "The boundaries between regions of different image types are known as critical curves.",
    "One can find them by computing where the eigenvalues of the curvature matrix change sign.",
    "In general, both eigenvalues will not change sign together, so that minima and maxima do not border each other and there is always a buffer of saddle points between them.",
    "One can map critical curves to the source plane via the lens equation, obtaining curves on the source plane, which are called caustics."
  ],
